1617084c-82d9-472f-ab44-c0f08cfb508e.43e7e28e-8a4e-404c-80f2-ca3651f1cf00.description=Run communication test on the given SA server or device group. This operation is supported from SA version 9.1 (sas91). Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. attachableName - The names of either the servers, or the device groups, separated by 'separator'. attachableID - The ids of either the servers, or the device groups, separated by 'separator'. If provided, the 'attachableName' will be ignored. attachableType - The type of the attachable items. Can be one of the following values\: SERVER or DEVICE_GROUP. timeout - Timeout in milliseconds, to wait for the job to finish. Default value is 0. separator - The separator used for separating the inputs. The default value for the separator is comma (,). Responses\: success - retrieved successfully failure - failed to retrieve data Returns\: returnResult - The id of the job created. 1617084c-82d9-472f-ab44-c0f08cfb508e.4daced54-0e0e-4e9f-9f20-4c5942a0cffc.description=Retrieves the output of a run communication test job. Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. jobId - The ID of the Run Communication Test job. separator - The separator used for separating the results. The default value for the separator is a comma (,). Outputs\: serverName - The names of the servers against which the run communication test job was ran. serverID - The IDs of the servers against which the run communication test job was ran. agentReachable - The flags indicating, for each server, if the SA agent is reachable. securityOK - The flags indicating if the encryption and security between each server and the SA core are OK. commandEngine - The flags indicating, for each server, if it can retrieve commands to be executed from the SA core. dataAccessEngine - The flags indicating, for each server, if it can retrieve its stored device information from the SA core. softwareRepository - The flags indicating, for each server, if it can retrieve software and patches from the SA core. machineID - The flags indicating, for each server, if its machine ID matches the one stored in the SA core. reachabilityTime - The reachability time, for each server. lifecycle - The lifecycle of each server. osVersion - The OS version of each server. Responses\: success - The operation has completed successfully. failure - The operation has failed. 1617084c-82d9-472f-ab44-c0f08cfb508e.7c40d213-6466-4d0b-8914-89985f07a146.description=Retrieves the server(s) ServerVO properties Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. agent - The agent name search string (can be a partial name and multiple return results can be returned; the matching type for this input can be selected by using the 'matching' flag). matching - A flag that indicates if the search performed using the agent name should be based on a partial or exact match. The default value for this input is 'Begins With'. serverID - The ID of the searched server. This input should be used for unique identification. If provided, then the 'agent' input is ignored. delimiter - The delimiter used to separate the result values. By default the values are comma delimited. Responses\: success - retrieved successfully failure - failed to retrieve data Returns\: createdBy - The name of the user who created this object. createdDate - The date that this object was created. id - The unique ID of this object. createdBy - The name of the user who created this object. createdDate - The date that this object was created. dirtyAttributes - A ; delimited list of attributes that are dirty (Modified and not yet fully propagated). modifiedBy - The user who last modified this object. modifiedDate - The date that this object was last modified on. description - The description of this object. hostname - The DNS hostname of this object. model - The model of this object. osVersion - The version of the OS running on the object. primaryIP - The primary IP address of this object. serialNumber - This object's serial number. manufacturer - The manufacturer of this object. name - The name of this object version - The version of this object codeset - The Code set of this object. customerName - The name of the customer this object was created for. defaultGW - The default gateway used when accessing this object. discoveredDate - The date when this object was first discovered. facilityName - The name of the facility housing this object. locale - The locale this object is in. lockComment - The comment on this object's locked. NOTE\: object may not be locked. lockDate - The date this object was last locked. lockUser - The user who locked this object last. isLocked - A boolean value specifying whether or not this object is currently locked. loopbackIP - The loopback ip address used by this object. managementIP - The management ip address used by this object. mid - mid The server's management identifier. NetBIOSName - The full netBIOS (Windows networking) name for this object. lifecycle - The state in the Opsware lifecycle that this object is currently in. origin - The origin of the managed server. ASSIMILATED or PROVISIONED osFlavor - The flavor of the OS running on this object. For example\: Windows. osSPVersion - The service pack version of the OS running on the object. peerIP - The managed server's peer IP address. platformName - The name of the platform. previousSWRegDate -The last time the Opsware agent reported the installed software on the server. realmName - The name of the realm this object is in. stage - The stage of the managed server. state - The current state of the managed server\: OK, UNREACHABLE or MAINTENANCE use - The intended use of the managed server (i.e. its role in a deployment)\: DEVELOPMENT, STAGING, PRODUCTION or UNKNOWN. virtualizationType - The virtualization type. 1617084c-82d9-472f-ab44-c0f08cfb508e.ad4f019a-3829-417e-9455-082d7e714de8.description=Sleeps for "X" seconds.

seconds - The number of seconds to sleep.

Responses\:
success - Slept for "X" seconds.
failure - was unable to sleep for some reason
1617084c-82d9-472f-ab44-c0f08cfb508e.daf264d0-8e6c-461d-b3ad-4b6a5bc9d390.description=
This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    matchType - The type of match to perform.
Valid values\: Exact Match, Contains, Contains Once, Does Not Contain, Match All Words, Match No Words, Regex
Default value\: Exact Match
    toMatch - The string that is checked for matching.
    matchTo - The string to match against.
Example\: If "matchType" is “RegEx”, the "matchTo" input is a regular expression such as\: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. 
    ignoreCase - Specifies whether to ignore case when matching or not.
Valid values\: False, True
Default value\: False

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
